metadata.name: Still Bored
metadata.description:
One day, while exploring the yacht club, Bongo stumbled upon a strange object - a shiny metal box with wires and buttons. He was immediately drawn to it and started pressing the buttons in excitement. Little did he know that the box was a high voltage control panel for the yacht's lighting system.

Suddenly, Bongo's finger slipped and landed on an exposed wire, sending a powerful electric shock through his body. His hair stood on end, and he turned vibrant colors of orange, blue, and yellow. Despite the shocking experience, Bongo was still bored.

Determined to find something to cure his boredom, Bongo continued to explore the yacht club. He tried playing with the sails, steering wheel, and even attempted to start the yacht's engine. But nothing seemed to satisfy him!...Bongo was Still Bored.
